               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184512150074"></xptr>
               <p>errand-boy. On the 5th of Dec, at twenty minutes before six o'clock in the evening, I saw a basket near the paper-bin in the shop—I looked into it, and saw some brass broken as this is now—the prisoner took it away, and I fol<lb></lb>lowed him—he went down by the New Church—I there asked him what he had got in the basket—he said, "Wet wood"—I said, "Let me look"—he said, "I will see you hanged first"—he ran off—I ran and took it from him—I found it was this brass—he said if I did not let him go he would stab me.</p>
